programme.title: The Librarian: Return to King Solomon's Mines
programme.desc: An adventurer (Noah Wyle) and a brilliant archaeologist (Gabrielle Anwar) use a map to search for the fabled mines of King Solomon.(n)

programme.title: The Librarian III: The Curse of the Judas Chalice
programme.desc: Unlikely adventurer Flynn Carsen sets out to protect a precious chalice from vampire Prince Vlad Dracul.(n)

programme.title: Killing Season
programme.desc: A U.S. veteran (Robert De Niro) and a former Serbian soldier (John Travolta) play cat-and-mouse games in the remote wilderness.(n)

programme.title: Blitz
programme.desc: A tough cop (Jason Statham) goes after a serial killer who targets police officers.(n)

Two planes almost collide after a blinding flash of light paralyzes air traffic controller Dylan Branson for a few seconds. Suspended from his job, Dylan starts to notice a repetition of sounds and events in his life at exactly the same time every day. An underlying pattern soon builds, drawing him into New York's Grand Central Station daily at 2:22 p.m. Now drawn into a complex relationship with a woman, Dylan must figure out a way to break the power of the past and take control of time itself.(n)

programme.title: Crossbow
programme.desc: William Tell competes in archery; guest Honor Blackman.(n)

programme.title: Transmorphers: Fall of Man
programme.desc: Robots from another world have descended on Earth, and they're not looking for a friendly exchange of ideas. Instead, they're intent on taking over the planet and destroying the human race. Police officer Ryan Hadley (Bruce Boxleitner) first notices something strange when his town is stricken by a wave of unusual deaths. The aliens, disguised as appliances, are responsible. As they make their true forms known, a small group of survivors bands together to fight back.(n)

programme.title: Farscape: The Peacekeeper Wars
programme.desc: John Crichton and his love Aeryn Sun are reunited; the wormhole knowledge that Crichton possesses makes him a target in an intergalactic war.(n)

programme.title: Farscape: The Peacekeeper Wars
programme.desc: With the birth of his child fast approaching, Crichton must find a way to use the wormhole technology to bring an end to the Scarran-Peacekeeper war.(n)

programme.title: Fallout
programme.desc: A Russian commander assumes control of a space station and faces a rebellious pilot (Daniel Baldwin) determined to stop him.(n)

programme.title: 2020 Fallen Earth
programme.desc: In a post oil-crash America, a 16-year-old runaway fights for his life while searching for his uncle's farm.(n)

programme.title: Hornet
programme.desc: An alien race that is intent on decimating mankind and repopulating Earth brainwashes humans to carry out acts of destruction. With the military powerless, humanity's only hope lies in an untested, hi-tech robot.(n)

programme.title: The Land That Time Forgot
programme.desc: After a violent storm causes their ship to founder, Frost Michaels (C. Thomas Howell) and Cole Stevens (Darren Dalton) find themselves on the shore of a strange island where dinosaurs coexist with humans. As they try not to become lunch for prehistoric carnivores, the pair also has to contend with the island's other residents -- namely, the crew of a Nazi U-boat who kidnapped Frost's girlfriend. And there's just one more thing: They have to figure out how to get back home.(n)

programme.title: Deadly Shooter
programme.desc: Cowboy Michael Atherton (Michael Dudikoff) intervenes on behalf of a prostitute, Wendy (Valerie Wildman), who is being terrorized by a gang of thugs. He guns down the attackers and shepherds her to safety. But the dead men's friends aren't about to forget what Michael did and are looking to get even. Michael considers his options, and several locals -- including card player Kyle (Randy Travis) -- offer their advice. But this dispute seems likely to be settled only by angry men and firearms.(n)

programme.title: Mercenary for Justice
programme.desc: As a mercenary, John Seeger (Steven Seagal) has a reputation that precedes him. That's why he's being blackmailed into performing a risky job: breaking the son of a wealthy arms dealer out of a South African prison. With his friends taken hostage, Seeger agrees to do the deed -- but finds out too late that he's been double-crossed. Not one who likes being taken for a fool, Seeger hatches an elaborate plan to get even that will make the prison break look like capture the flag.(n)

programme.title: Beyond the Law
programme.desc: A former mobster turned businessman and a police detective must contend with a dirty ex-cop looking to bring the killer of his son to justice.(n)

programme.title: Phantom Punch
programme.desc: Ex-convict Sonny Liston (Ving Rhames) becomes the world heavyweight boxing champion in 1962, but his personal life is marred by run-ins with organized crime and the law.(n)

programme.title: The Iceman
programme.desc: Hit man Richard Kuklinski (Michael Shannon) earns a well-deserved reputation as a cold-blooded killer but manages to keep his violent profession a secret from his wife (Winona Ryder) and children for years.(n)

programme.title: Animal
programme.desc: In this crime-drama starring football superstar Jim Brown, a notorious gangster must reconcile his past in order to make a future for his criminally-minded son.(n)

programme.title: Crossbow
programme.desc: Unless Tell rescues a peeress, Gessler will take her land.(n)

programme.title: Love and Bullets
programme.desc: The FBI sends a loner (Charles Bronson) to kidnap a mobster's (Rod Steiger) mistress (Jill Ireland) in Switzerland.(n)

programme.title: Borderline
programme.desc: A U.S. Border Patrol officer (Charles Bronson) poses as an illegal alien to catch a killer (Ed Harris) smuggling laborers from Mexico.(n)

programme.title: King Solomon's Mines
programme.desc: A renowned adventurer leads a dangerous quest to find a woman's father, who disappeared in Africa while searching for the fabled mines.(n)

programme.title: King Solomon's Mines

programme.title: Prairie Fever
programme.desc: Preston Biggs (Kevin Sorbo), the former sheriff of a small Wild West town, is reeling from the death of his wife and has succumbed to the bottle. He gets a chance at redemption when he is asked to escort three women (Jillian Armenante, Dominique Swain, Felicia Day) from the prairie back to civilization. Along the way, they meet Olivia (Jamie Anne Allman), an outlaw desperately on the run from her former partner (Lance Henriksen). Preston must pick himself up and defend all the women.(n)

programme.title: Flyboys
programme.desc: Before the United States enters World War I, some American youths volunteer for the French military. Subsequently, they become the first U.S. fighter pilots and form a squadron known as the Lafayette Escadrille, whose exploits and heroism become the stuff of legend.(n)

programme.title: Dam999
programme.desc: Two mariners return home after several years of traveling.(n)

programme.title: The Code
programme.desc: A veteran thief (Morgan Freeman) recruits a novice (Antonio Banderas) to pull off one last job to repay Russian gangsters.(n)

programme.title: Buscando a Frida
programme.desc: Frida, de 16 años, hija mayor del multimillonario Abelardo Pons (Eduardo Santamarina), desaparece la noche del cumpleaños de su padre, bajo muy extrañas circunstancias. La vida de la familia cambia para siempre: de una, aparentemente feliz y perfecta, pasan a una donde se revelan secretos, surgen conflictos y mentiras. Todos se convierten en sospechosos, pero nadie espera el impactante giro que tomará la historia, cuando tratan de ocultar la verdad. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: El día
programme.desc: Un programa informativo, de opinión y entrevistas, conducido por el veterano periodista Huchi Lora y su potente equipo, quienes asumen la responsabilidad de llevar a los televidentes la actualidad informativa y el análisis de la noticia tanto de República Dominicana como el mundo.(n)

programme.title: Telematutino 11
programme.desc: Programa de televisión matutino bajo la conducción de Ramón Núñez y Jacqueline Morel. En este espacio, los conductores se encargarán de darle al televidente una panorámica de las noticias nacionales e internacionales más relevantes del momento. Así mismo, se entrevistan a diversas personalidades del mundo político, económico y artístico.(n)

programme.title: Avengers Assemble
programme.desc: "Los Vengadores Unidos" reúne al equipo de súper héroes más popular - Iron Man, Hulk, Capitán América, Thor, Ojo de Halcón y la Viuda Negra, junto con el recién llegado Halcón, siendo la primera vez en la historia de la animación que este heterogéneo grupo de héroes une sus fuerzas. Dirigido por Iron Man, los héroes entrenan y viven juntos en su nueva sede en la Torre Vengadores.(n)

programme.desc: Neriman vive con su padre y su tía desde que perdió a su madre cuando era solo una niña. En el humilde barrio de Fatih, en Estambul, los tres les dan pelea a una dura vida. La joven sueña con llegar lejos, tener un buen trabajo y ayudar a su familia. Está de novia con Sinasi, un joven trabajador con el que quiere casarse. Sin embargo, la relación pronto empieza a desmoronarse.(n)

programme.title: Amor Comprado
programme.desc: Una muchacha acepta casarse con un millonario para liberar a su padre y cuidar a su hermano. Elegida entre varias mujeres, la joven debe ir a una cita a conocer a su futuro esposo, pero cuando se pierde y llega muy tarde conoce a otro joven en el camino. Ambos se enamoran a primera vista sin darse cuenta de que el otro es quien ha entrado en el contrato del matrimonio arreglado y tendrán que superar varios obstáculos antes de poder vivir felices.(n)

programme.title: Buscando a Frida
programme.desc: Frida, de 16 años, hija mayor del multimillonario Abelardo Pons (Eduardo Santamarina), desaparece la noche del cumpleaños de su padre, bajo muy extrañas circunstancias. La vida de la familia cambia para siempre: de una, aparentemente feliz y perfecta, pasan a una donde se revelan secretos, surgen conflictos y mentiras. programme.title: Franz Ferdinand at Rockenheim Festival 2013
programme.desc: Franz Ferdinand -lo mejor de Escocia- formó parte del renacimiento post-punk de mediados de la década de 2000 junto con The Arctic Monkeys y Kaiser Chiefs. Su debut entró directamente en el número 3 de las listas británicas, y la banda ganó el Mercury Music Prize de 2004, dos premios BRIT en 2005 al mejor grupo británico y al mejor acto de rock británico, y NME nombró a Franz Ferdinand como su álbum del año.
